se. In focusing on this Global South context, Chaudhry makes novel arguments about the development of intimacy within marriages that are inherently unequal and even violent, thereby offering an alternative to Euro-American understandings of intimacy and women's agency.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Anthropology. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aSociology : Geography. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Marriage & Family.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848559140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438485591423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438485591/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles